1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a cross-blockchain transfer protocol, which involves security and cryptography aspects. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed protocol involves decentralized transfer of tokens between multiple blockchains, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
3. cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) - Similar to the above reasoning, the paper proposes a protocol for decentralized transfer of tokens between multiple blockchains, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed protocol involves communication and data exchange between different blockchains, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for cross-blockchain token transfers, which involves control and management aspects.
